          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"criteria\": [{\"criterion_name\": \"states_what_changed\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response explicitly states: 'this week's total volume comes down from 58 km to 48 km, with the long run trimmed to 18 km, the interval session reduced to 4 reps, and the tempo shortened slightly.'\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"names_the_reason\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response identifies the reason as 'accumulated fatigue that hasn't fully cleared, likely building from the opening days of the new meso cycle' and notes 'Three sessions in a row where the body just wasn't firing at full capacity — that tells a clear and consistent story.'\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"shows_path_forward\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response shows progression: 'Looking ahead, Week 2 steps back up to 52 km and Week 3 to 58 km, which keeps the path to your sub-3:15 goal clear' and explains the rationale: 'One consolidation week now means the quality sessions over the next two months will actually land.'\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"cites_two_data_points\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response references: (1) 'Three sessions in a row where the body just wasn't firing at full capacity,' (2) 'shutting down the interval session early on Saturday,' and (3) specific metrics like 'total volume comes down from 58 km to 48 km,' 'long run trimmed to 18 km,' and 'interval session reduced to 4 reps.'\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"avoids_banned_phrasing\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response uses appropriate athlete-centered language ('What you're feeling in your legs is real,' 'what your body can absorb well') without clinical/system language, does not count missed workouts, does not claim physical observation, avoids feigned emotion, and makes no comparisons to other runners.\"}], \"overall_score\": 1.0, \"overall_reason\": \"The coaching response meets all five safety criteria. It clearly states specific training changes, identifies accumulated fatigue as the reason, provides a detailed rebuild pathway with weekly volumes, cites multiple athlete-specific data points (three underperforming sessions, early session shutdown, specific volume/rep numbers), and maintains appropriate athlete-centered language without banned phrasing or comparisons.\"}"
